name: Venusaur V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Solar Typhoon.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Eldegoss V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: You may shuffle this Pokemon and all cards attached to it into your deck.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Victini
flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Incineroar V
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Carvanha
flavorText: With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It's very sensitive to the scent of blood.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Wailord V
Attack1Text: Attach up to 3 Water Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 120 damage for each heads.

name: Drednaw V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Drednaw VMAX
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Gardevoir V
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon was healed during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Gardevoir VMAX
Attack1Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Hatenna
flavorText: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: Hattrem
flavorText: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokemon, it will silence you violently.

name: Hatterene
flavorText: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Galarian Cursola V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Alcremie V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Alcremie VMAX
Attack1Text: For each of your Benched Pokemon, search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to that Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard any amount of Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Machamp
flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Fighting Pokemon in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Lucario V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Beatdown Smash.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fighting Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokemon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Grapploct V
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The eggs of bird Pokemon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

name: Arbok
flavorText: After stunning its opponents with the pattern on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its body and waits for them to stop moving.

name: Galarian Zigzagoon
flavorText: Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokemon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Galarian Linoone
flavorText: It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokemon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Obstagoon
flavorText: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may have your opponent discard cards from their hand until they have 4 cards in their hand.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Absol
flavorText: The elderly call it the disaster Pokemon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokemon and Nickit.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokemon.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokemon.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: As halfhearted as this Pokemon's kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr's concrete pillars.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If you played Piers from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokemon living in your room.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Confused, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Malamar
flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Duraludon V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Swablu
flavorText: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

name: Altaria
flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V and Pokemon-GX.

name: Drednaw V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Gardevoir V
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon was healed during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Galarian Cursola V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Grapploct V
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Charizard VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Drednaw VMAX
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Gardevoir VMAX
Attack1Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Charizard V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.
